WEBVTT

00:02.703 --> 00:04.398
Hey, guys, guess what.

00:04.571 --> 00:07.596
Tomorrow is Dan's birthday.

00:09.810 --> 00:13.007
So I was thinking, why don't we give him
a surprise birthday party?

00:13.480 --> 00:15.676
Because we all hate him.

00:16.683 --> 00:18.151
Oh, yeah, right.

00:18.318 --> 00:21.310
On the other hand, if we start treating Dan
like a human being...

00:21.488 --> 00:23.422
...maybe he'll start acting like one.

00:23.824 --> 00:26.953
Really. Really. Mrs. Claus caught him
with one of the lady elves...

00:27.127 --> 00:29.357
...in back of the sleigh.

00:30.864 --> 00:32.764
[MIMICS GUNSHOT]

00:32.933 --> 00:37.234
Preliminary hearing's next week.
Tell all your little friends.

00:38.171 --> 00:40.936
You were saying, sir?

00:41.108 --> 00:45.272
What do you say we all chip in
and get him a serious wound?

00:46.446 --> 00:48.881
- Hey, guys.
MAC: Hey, Leon.

00:49.049 --> 00:52.451
- I'm gonna do my homework now, Harry.
- Great. Did you clean up your room?

00:52.619 --> 00:53.643
Yes, sir.

00:53.820 --> 00:56.846
But I think I used too much wax
on the carpet. Ha.

00:57.724 --> 00:59.158
[MAC 8. CHRISTINE CHUCKLE]

01:00.494 --> 01:04.623
- Anybody need a vacuum?
- You know, I really do admire you, sir.

01:04.798 --> 01:07.961
Taking care of a boy that age
is a big responsibility.

01:08.135 --> 01:10.604
Someday.
I plan to have a family of my own.

01:10.771 --> 01:13.763
Hi, Mac.
My family just came in from Vietnam...

01:13.941 --> 01:16.842
...and they've decided to live with us.

01:21.448 --> 01:24.076
Ask and ye shall receive.

01:24.251 --> 01:25.514
[LAUGHS]

01:27.000 --> 01:33.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:13.934 --> 02:14.958
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

02:15.135 --> 02:17.001
Yeah?

02:17.170 --> 02:20.572
Sir, I just picked up the birthday cake
for Dan's surprise party tonight.

02:20.741 --> 02:23.301
- Great. Let's have a look.
- Okay, sir.

02:24.678 --> 02:26.908
But hold onto your hat.

02:28.582 --> 02:32.712
I had it made
at one of those X-rated bakeries.

02:39.626 --> 02:42.891
- Is that--?
- Strawberry cream, yes, sir.

02:45.298 --> 02:49.201
- You think Dan will like it?
- I think he'll many it.

02:50.537 --> 02:53.006
DAN: Harry.
- Gotta go.

02:53.273 --> 02:54.468
[DAN CLAPS]

02:54.641 --> 02:59.442
Oh, ha, ha, guess what. Go ahead.
Take the wildest guess you can think of.

02:59.613 --> 03:03.846
Morley Safer
is doing a plate-spinning act in Vegas?

03:04.584 --> 03:07.986
Okay, take the second wildest guess
you can think of.

03:08.155 --> 03:12.023
- Well, I'm afraid it involves Morley again.
- Never mind.

03:13.160 --> 03:17.324
Finally got a date
with that nympho in Xerox.

03:18.799 --> 03:21.234
- Really?
- She's from California.

03:21.401 --> 03:24.371
- Oh, Dan.
- California.

03:24.538 --> 03:28.236
I'm not even gonna have
to buy her dinner.

03:30.277 --> 03:32.678
I'm real happy for you, Dan.

03:32.846 --> 03:35.281
Why don't you bring her
by my apartment tonight, huh?

03:35.949 --> 03:39.283
I'd like to go it alone this time.
Maybe next week, huh?

03:39.453 --> 03:41.285
Dan.

03:44.124 --> 03:47.458
I'm having a surprise birthday party
for you tonight.

03:47.627 --> 03:48.651
Huh?

03:52.299 --> 03:54.165
A surprise party? For me?

03:56.470 --> 04:00.464
Harry, no one has ever done anything
like that for me before in my life.

04:00.640 --> 04:05.168
No one has ever cared that much.

04:05.512 --> 04:07.640
Maybe some other time.

04:07.814 --> 04:12.047
Dan, I went out on a limb for you
on this one.

04:12.586 --> 04:14.452
- What about my date?
- Bring her along.

04:14.621 --> 04:19.252
- Uh, she only eats health food.
<i>- We'll</i> have hay.

04:20.560 --> 04:21.789
[SIGHS]

04:34.241 --> 04:35.606
Here's your coffee.

04:35.776 --> 04:40.236
Look at them over there,
smiling and laughing...

04:40.714 --> 04:44.412
...and wondering what's in my refrigerator
they missed.

04:45.619 --> 04:50.056
- They didn't bring anything with them?
- A sacred calf.

04:50.590 --> 04:51.853
Oh.

04:52.025 --> 04:55.723
That kind of puts the damper on rib night,
then, doesn't it?

04:56.363 --> 04:58.889
If only they didn't follow me to work.

04:59.065 --> 05:02.057
Oh, come on.
I bet they're just proud of you.

05:02.536 --> 05:04.300
Watch this.

05:05.505 --> 05:06.631
[WHIRRING]

05:14.214 --> 05:17.616
They must go to pieces when you file.

05:19.586 --> 05:20.815
DAN:
Okay. Ha, ha.

05:20.987 --> 05:26.084
Now, I got us a room at this quaint little
18th-century inn on Long Island.

05:26.259 --> 05:28.557
Wow, totally awesome.

05:28.995 --> 05:31.054
I beg your pardon?

05:31.231 --> 05:32.960
Just don't forget, Danny...

05:33.133 --> 05:36.364
...my sexual biorhythms
hit their apex at midnight.

05:36.536 --> 05:38.368
Midnight.

05:38.538 --> 05:40.973
What happens at, uh, 12:01?

05:41.374 --> 05:45.072
Heh. Remember Cinderella?

05:47.080 --> 05:48.980
Cinderella.

05:49.149 --> 05:51.550
Her two ugly stepsisters.

05:51.718 --> 05:53.686
All right, bring them.

05:57.891 --> 06:00.326
<i>“</i> Remove watch.“

06:04.130 --> 06:07.532
“Put watch in magic bag.“

06:09.703 --> 06:12.468
“Hit watch with hammer.“

06:17.644 --> 06:19.271
“Twice.“

06:24.284 --> 06:26.048
“Caution:

06:26.219 --> 06:30.247
Do not hit watch with hammer really.

06:31.958 --> 06:37.124
Read chapter 14,
'Palming the Phony Watch.”

06:41.268 --> 06:42.736
Aw.

06:43.870 --> 06:47.170
Evening, sir.
I've got the party favors for tonight.

06:47.340 --> 06:48.466
Swell.

06:48.642 --> 06:53.842
Some of them are, uh.
a little bit, um, naughty. Ha, ha.

06:55.282 --> 06:58.274
Really? Let's have a look.

07:02.789 --> 07:05.781
Couple of toads playing leapfrog?

07:08.762 --> 07:11.060
Is that what they're doing?

07:12.032 --> 07:13.693
Afraid so.

07:13.867 --> 07:16.359
Well, it's the thought that counts.

07:17.671 --> 07:18.695
[DOOR CLOSES]

07:18.872 --> 07:21.773
I want them dead.

07:22.175 --> 07:23.643
Mac, what happened?

07:23.810 --> 07:28.805
Quon Le's family declared my lunch hour
as a religious holiday.

07:28.982 --> 07:32.612
- Oh, where are they now?
- Blessing the salad bar.

07:33.787 --> 07:37.246
- I've been there. It couldn't hurt.
- Sir, I gotta talk to somebody.

07:37.424 --> 07:39.825
I'm afraid I may do something drastic.

07:39.993 --> 07:42.690
I mean, Quon Le's family
acts as if my sole role in life...

07:42.862 --> 07:44.830
...is to cater to their every need.

07:45.165 --> 07:49.227
Well, yeah, Mac, in all fairness, they should
be willing to make some kind of sacrifice.

07:49.402 --> 07:52.565
Oh, they did.
Guess who had to clean it up.

07:54.474 --> 07:57.535
Mac, maybe I could help.
I could talk to them at the party tonight.

07:57.711 --> 07:59.179
At the party tonight?

07:59.346 --> 08:02.976
You invited Quon Le's family
to the party tonight?

08:05.151 --> 08:06.243
Yeah.

08:07.354 --> 08:09.220
Didn't wanna be rude.

08:09.389 --> 08:12.222
They'll probably bring the cattle.

08:14.427 --> 08:16.327
Hay it is.

08:30.643 --> 08:31.667
Shh.

08:31.845 --> 08:33.506
[WHISPERS]
<i>He's</i> coming.

08:37.517 --> 08:38.609
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

08:40.453 --> 08:42.421
ALL:
Surprise!

08:43.722 --> 08:45.350
[YELLS]

08:46.159 --> 08:50.460
Friends. What can I say but thank you?

08:55.168 --> 08:57.000
Gotta go. Bye.

08:57.170 --> 08:59.366
Not on your life.

08:59.539 --> 09:04.136
You are about to witness
The Amazing Harry...

09:04.310 --> 09:08.338
...with his prestidigitation wizardry.
Ha, ha.

09:08.515 --> 09:09.710
[SPEAKING IN FRENCH]

09:09.883 --> 09:12.978
Oh, thank you. I'm starved.

09:14.788 --> 09:19.123
- Come on, we'll go swish it in the dip.
- Everybody, take a seat, take a seat.

09:19.292 --> 09:20.691
Tonight, I will be assisted...

09:20.860 --> 09:24.262
...by the very able and lovely
and ever-present Mr. Leoni.

09:24.431 --> 09:25.796
[ALL APPLAUDING]

09:28.001 --> 09:29.594
He made me do it.

09:29.769 --> 09:33.103
How about a little magic music,
Mr. Leoni?

09:33.406 --> 09:35.932
[HORN BLARING]

09:37.110 --> 09:40.808
That's plenty of the magic music, Mr. Leoni.
I need the magic ball.

09:40.980 --> 09:43.608
I need the magic bucket.

09:44.451 --> 09:47.113
And now, friends, watch.

09:47.287 --> 09:51.520
Watch as the magic ball
makes its mysterious journey.

09:51.691 --> 09:53.989
Look. Look.

09:54.160 --> 09:59.621
It floats, and it flies, and it--

09:59.799 --> 10:02.427
Bares us to tears.

10:02.602 --> 10:05.469
Come on, people, I'm working here.

10:05.872 --> 10:07.670
We'll skip the magic ball for the moment.

10:07.841 --> 10:09.639
[CHRISTINE LAUGHS]

10:09.809 --> 10:13.245
- Well, I thought that was cute.
- Look, he's taking out something else.

10:13.413 --> 10:16.405
<i>Oh,</i> God, <i>let it be a TV Guide.</i>

10:17.450 --> 10:20.181
A traditional classic,
always a crowd pleaser...

10:20.353 --> 10:21.616
...the rabbit from the hat.

10:21.788 --> 10:22.812
[GASPS]

10:22.989 --> 10:25.720
Look, there's a little hair. Ha-ha-ha.

10:27.460 --> 10:29.360
But seriously, folks.

10:29.529 --> 10:32.396
Sir, would you examine the hat
and see it is absolutely empty?

10:33.166 --> 10:36.796
Is it safe to assume
these aren't Raisinets?

10:38.037 --> 10:39.971
Oh, God.

10:42.609 --> 10:47.638
There will be a short intermission while
Mr. Leoni and I prepare for the grand finale.

10:49.149 --> 10:52.050
- What time is it, Danny?
- Uh, 9:37.

10:52.218 --> 10:53.549
[SIGHS]

10:54.187 --> 10:56.451
- I think it's beginning.
- Oh, no, don't start without me.

10:56.623 --> 10:58.148
[PANTING]

10:58.324 --> 11:01.089
- Yes. Yes, I'm on my upward curve.
- I'm not.

11:01.261 --> 11:03.127
Just wait. I'll get you some punch.

11:03.296 --> 11:07.028
- Wait, no. Come with me to the bowl.
- Okay.

11:07.200 --> 11:08.725
[SPEAKING IN VIETNAMESE]

11:08.902 --> 11:10.927
Uh, Fritos.

11:13.339 --> 11:15.740
[SPEAKING IN VIETNAMESE]

11:17.744 --> 11:19.644
Onion dip.

11:22.815 --> 11:24.749
Oh, no.

11:24.918 --> 11:26.647
“Oh, no," what?

11:26.819 --> 11:30.016
Grandmother Duc says she's very sorry
about your TV set.

11:30.190 --> 11:31.589
She had no idea.

11:32.392 --> 11:36.852
- What about my TV set?
- She said she didn't know what it was.

11:37.030 --> 11:40.466
She thought evil spirits
had invaded our furniture.

11:40.633 --> 11:43.534
- And...?
- She released them.

11:43.703 --> 11:45.467
- With...?
- A Sledgehammer.

11:45.638 --> 11:47.037
[SHRIEKS]

11:47.674 --> 11:51.372
HARRY:
And here it is, friends, the magic box.

11:51.544 --> 11:55.071
- That is it.
- It sure as shooting is, Mac.

11:55.248 --> 11:57.808
Miss Sullivan, enter Ia magic box.

11:57.984 --> 12:01.750
I didn't say anything
when they planted crops in my bathtub.

12:02.322 --> 12:04.017
CHRISTINE:
Kind of small in there, isn't it?

12:04.190 --> 12:07.592
I didn't say anything when they constructed
a shrine in my garage.

12:07.760 --> 12:09.558
Just one leg at a time.

12:09.729 --> 12:13.962
But they touched my TV.

12:14.334 --> 12:15.995
Okay. What do I do now?

12:16.169 --> 12:19.730
All you have to do is scream
when I cut through your vital organs.

12:19.906 --> 12:21.340
[SCREAMS]

12:21.741 --> 12:24.472
- Just like that.
- What's the matter?

12:24.644 --> 12:29.582
I feel the tortured souls of my ancestors
crying out in agony.

12:31.017 --> 12:32.610
Okay.

12:33.219 --> 12:37.918
I don't wanna hear any more
of this tortured-ancestral-soul jive talk.

12:38.091 --> 12:42.187
Now watch as I ram the blades
through her body.

12:42.362 --> 12:45.332
Now we're talking fun.

12:45.498 --> 12:49.901
- I want them out!
- You have dishonored my family.

12:50.069 --> 12:52.197
Do you realize what this means?

12:52.372 --> 12:58.106
And though she appears to be whole,
she is indeed half.

12:59.145 --> 13:00.442
My legs.

13:00.613 --> 13:04.379
Oh, Christine,
would you please stop whining?

13:08.354 --> 13:10.186
Hello?

13:12.592 --> 13:14.082
Mrs. Lund.

13:14.260 --> 13:15.955
Oh, heh.

13:17.130 --> 13:20.293
Miss Sullivan, you know Mrs. Lund
from Juvenile Services?

13:20.466 --> 13:22.560
Oh, yeah, hi.

13:23.836 --> 13:29.104
- Hi.
- I want these evil spirits put back in my TV!

13:29.976 --> 13:32.035
So, what brings you
to our neighborhood, huh?

13:32.211 --> 13:36.011
Harry, she's in a sexual trance.
I need ice.

13:36.182 --> 13:39.311
- In the bucket next to the freezer.
- Right.

13:41.321 --> 13:46.851
Well, as you know, our agency requires us
to make these surprise inspections--

13:47.026 --> 13:50.792
Sir, I'm afraid they're gonna
start flinging the weenies around.

13:51.664 --> 13:54.190
- Put them up, huh, Bull?
- Check.

13:55.168 --> 13:57.796
"To ensure that our foster children
are being exposed...

13:57.970 --> 13:59.597
...to a suitable environment.

13:59.772 --> 14:03.140
[SPEAKING IN VIETNAMESE]

14:03.309 --> 14:07.473
My family says
they are going to kill themselves.

14:12.118 --> 14:15.577
Have I come at a bad time?

14:21.994 --> 14:27.398
I'm sorry, but did those people
say something about killing themselves?

14:30.136 --> 14:33.003
It did sound like that, didn't it?

14:33.172 --> 14:36.665
- Where is Leon?
LEON: Right here.

14:41.814 --> 14:44.749
Did I mention that he has his own room?

14:49.021 --> 14:52.685
I see he has his own nylons
and heels too.

14:53.760 --> 14:58.254
Mrs. Lund. I know how all this must look,
but believe me, I can explain everything.

15:00.166 --> 15:04.660
- I'm hereto strip for Dan Fielding.
- In the kitchen.

15:06.172 --> 15:08.334
You see, Mrs. Lund, we--

15:08.508 --> 15:09.532
Yeah?

15:09.709 --> 15:13.111
My family would like to know
if this is a good time to slay themselves.

15:13.279 --> 15:14.769
Sure.

15:14.947 --> 15:19.817
I mean, no. No. No slay self.

15:19.986 --> 15:23.422
Try cheese log.

15:24.424 --> 15:27.257
Sir? Sir? I think my tendons
are beginning to snap.

15:27.427 --> 15:28.519
Huh?

15:29.629 --> 15:32.189
Open magic box.

15:32.365 --> 15:33.662
Right.

15:34.100 --> 15:35.124
- Hey, Harry.
HARRY: Yeah?

15:35.301 --> 15:36.826
Where do you keep the mustard?

15:37.003 --> 15:39.734
How can you think of your stomach
at a time like this?

15:39.906 --> 15:43.035
Easy. There's no food at my house.

15:43.443 --> 15:46.413
My family is preparing to die.

15:46.579 --> 15:48.513
Those are butter knives.

15:48.681 --> 15:51.878
What are they gonna do,
spread themselves to death?

15:54.153 --> 16:00.024
Uh, uh, uh, you ought to try these
knee-highs. They're so practical.

16:00.726 --> 16:02.956
Happy birthday.

16:03.129 --> 16:05.223
- She's for you.
DAN: Heh.

16:05.398 --> 16:08.163
You pop the red ones,
it's 20 bucks extra.

16:08.334 --> 16:12.396
- Dan, it's 10:15. Time to start.
- Gotta run.

16:12.572 --> 16:15.667
- Not till after the cake.
- Bull, please.

16:15.842 --> 16:19.005
She's from California.

16:19.879 --> 16:21.438
Oh, yeah?

16:24.016 --> 16:26.007
Would you read my script?

16:27.787 --> 16:30.449
- It's stuck.
CHRISTINE: What's stuck?

16:30.623 --> 16:31.920
The magic box.

16:32.091 --> 16:35.891
- Oh, uh, can we keep her?
HARRY: Leon.

16:36.429 --> 16:38.420
Unless Mrs. Lund doesn't mind.

16:38.598 --> 16:42.728
- Mac, you must apologize to them.
- For what?

16:42.902 --> 16:47.999
Wanting to live with my own wife
in my own livestock-free house?

16:48.174 --> 16:50.472
You have offended Grandfather Ho.

16:50.643 --> 16:53.635
You're lucky
I haven't poached Grandfather Ho.

16:54.013 --> 16:56.539
- Now, I have had it. Do you understand?
- Hey, hey, hey.

16:56.716 --> 16:59.242
Wait a minute. He wants to speak.

17:00.419 --> 17:01.784
Ho?

17:01.954 --> 17:03.513
[GROANING]

17:09.929 --> 17:11.657
What'd he say?

17:14.400 --> 17:16.266
Don't worry, Quon Le,
help is on the way.

17:16.435 --> 17:19.665
I'm so frightened.
His heart stopped beating.

17:19.839 --> 17:22.171
Well, it's ticking again.

17:22.340 --> 17:25.071
Oh, God bless you, Harry.

17:25.243 --> 17:29.112
Actually, Quon Le,
Mac saved your grandfather's life.

17:29.849 --> 17:32.750
Uh, I spilled some punch.

17:35.154 --> 17:36.178
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

17:36.355 --> 17:37.584
Yeah, who is it?

17:40.192 --> 17:42.752
- Fire department.
- Come in.

17:43.796 --> 17:47.357
There she is. Don't worry, little lady.
we'll have you out in just a minute.

17:47.533 --> 17:50.127
No, no, no.
It's the Asian gentleman in my bedroom.

17:50.303 --> 17:54.399
The Asian gentleman in your bedroom.
Right. Let's go.

17:54.874 --> 17:57.434
- And use the door.
FIREMAN: Right.

17:58.311 --> 17:59.710
It's 11:59.

17:59.879 --> 18:00.903
[DAN SIGHS]

18:01.080 --> 18:03.549
Oh, gosh. I'm awfully warm.

18:03.716 --> 18:04.740
[DAN CHUCKLES]

18:04.917 --> 18:08.979
Danny? Oh, Danny, I'm peaking.

18:09.155 --> 18:12.284
Oh, no, no, no, you das-- Don't. I...

18:12.458 --> 18:14.790
Oh, look, the snorkel truck. Uh--

18:15.661 --> 18:19.222
Hey, you, with the hose, bring it up here.

18:20.232 --> 18:25.033
Danny. Danny. Oh, Danny.

18:25.671 --> 18:28.038
Well, I gotta go, Dan. Goodbye.

18:28.941 --> 18:30.500
Wait a minute.

18:30.676 --> 18:33.407
Are you telling me the mood is gone
just like that?

18:33.579 --> 18:35.172
- Totally.
- Ugh.

18:35.348 --> 18:39.342
But don't worry,
I peak again in the spring.

18:41.220 --> 18:42.654
DAN:
Uh, but...

18:42.822 --> 18:45.655
Wait. We've got hay.

18:49.962 --> 18:51.259
Cake?

19:00.773 --> 19:02.571
It's better than nothing.

19:04.410 --> 19:06.538
Come on, I'll buy you a drink.

19:08.648 --> 19:12.243
I don't know what the problem was,
but the old man is fine now.

19:12.418 --> 19:15.217
By the way.
that's a nasty punch stain on your carpet.

19:15.388 --> 19:19.416
Yeah. While you're here, would you help me
get this girl out of the box? It's stuck.

19:19.592 --> 19:21.185
Sure. Why not?

19:21.360 --> 19:24.193
Phil, go get the Jaws of Life.

19:24.730 --> 19:27.893
- The Jaws of Life?
- Big tools for big jobs.

19:28.067 --> 19:29.557
[LAUGHS]

19:30.403 --> 19:31.427
Oh.

19:31.604 --> 19:34.164
- What? Did I break it?
- Well, no, no, you opened it.

19:34.340 --> 19:35.933
CHRISTINE:
Get me out!

19:36.876 --> 19:38.901
QUON LE: Mac.
- Punch all over me.

19:39.078 --> 19:40.807
I said I was sorry.

19:40.980 --> 19:43.950
- Oh, Mac, you saved Grandfather's life.
- Hmm.

19:44.116 --> 19:45.140
[MAC SIGHS]

19:45.317 --> 19:48.014
How could we ever repay you?

19:48.487 --> 19:52.617
Oh, don't worry, Quon Le.

19:54.527 --> 19:57.724
Although a TV would be nice.

19:59.865 --> 20:02.266
I have no feeling below the waist.

20:02.435 --> 20:04.130
Need some help?

20:06.872 --> 20:10.672
- No, thank you.
- Right.

20:11.677 --> 20:13.645
- Can I go now?
- Sure.

20:13.813 --> 20:15.941
Thanks, ML, uh...?

20:16.115 --> 20:19.050
They call me Bull.

20:20.186 --> 20:22.814
That's what they all say.

20:24.356 --> 20:25.755
As long as you're all right...

20:25.925 --> 20:29.122
...I better stop Phil
from dragging up the Jaws of Life.

20:29.295 --> 20:30.785
HARRY:
Yeah.

20:30.963 --> 20:36.026
Oh, yeah. Ha, ha.
she went down real easy, didn't she?

20:37.303 --> 20:40.238
- Couch.
- Oh, yeah. Right.

20:43.008 --> 20:45.636
[SPEAKING IN VIETNAMESE]

20:46.112 --> 20:47.546
Hi, Ho.

20:48.981 --> 20:51.416
[SPEAKING IN VIETNAMESE]

20:52.051 --> 20:54.315
- Translation?
- He says you're a hero.

20:54.487 --> 20:55.886
- Oh, yeah?
HO: Ha, ha.

20:56.055 --> 20:57.819
[SPEAKING IN VIETNAMESE]

20:57.990 --> 20:59.788
He says he owes you his life.

20:59.959 --> 21:02.018
And in our country,
when a man saves your life...

21:02.194 --> 21:04.060
...you grant him anything he wishes.

21:04.230 --> 21:05.254
Anything at all?

21:05.431 --> 21:06.455
[SPEAKS IN VIETNAMESE]

21:06.899 --> 21:10.733
Grandfather says he knows what you want.
You want them to leave.

21:10.903 --> 21:12.997
It is done.

21:13.172 --> 21:14.833
- You mean they're moving out?
- Heh, yes.

21:15.007 --> 21:17.840
All right. All right.

21:18.010 --> 21:20.411
I can't put them on the streets.
Where will they go?

21:20.579 --> 21:24.573
Uh, presidential suite, Regency Hotel.

21:25.084 --> 21:28.076
Did I mention Grandfather speaks English?

21:28.254 --> 21:29.551
ALL:
No.

21:29.922 --> 21:34.325
Well, ha, ha, thanks for caring, Mac.
but money is no problem.

21:34.493 --> 21:36.894
I'm stinking rich.

21:37.997 --> 21:41.490
- Well, why did you wanna stay with us?
- Well, ancient tradition.

21:41.667 --> 21:45.160
It would be an insult not to. Hey.

21:45.337 --> 21:49.001
Some tradition. Sex rocks, don't it?

21:50.142 --> 21:54.238
- What about that heart attack?
- Gotta go now. See you later.

21:54.413 --> 21:56.438
Yo, Ho.

22:00.853 --> 22:02.753
You planned this whole thing, didn't you?

22:02.922 --> 22:03.946
[CHUCKLES]

22:04.123 --> 22:05.318
<i>Moi?</i>

22:06.792 --> 22:09.625
You sly old devil.

22:09.795 --> 22:12.765
But how did you know it was Mac
who would come to your rescue?

22:12.932 --> 22:17.096
For many years during the war,
Mac took care of my family in Vietnam.

22:17.269 --> 22:19.966
<i>He's</i> a caring, compassionate man.

22:20.139 --> 22:24.838
Now, figuring that out was, uh.
no magic.

22:33.686 --> 22:36.485
Naughty bunny.

22:40.693 --> 22:42.161
So as you can see, Mrs. Lund...

22:42.328 --> 22:45.525
...it really was an incredible string
of coincidences.

22:45.998 --> 22:49.366
Yeah. Well, Judge Stone, ha, ha.
I can't quite believe it...

22:49.535 --> 22:53.130
...but you do seem to successfully
have explained everything.

22:53.305 --> 22:55.569
And it's all true, every word of it.

22:55.741 --> 22:58.210
Mrs. Lund, I want you to know that,
for Leon's sake...

22:58.377 --> 23:01.403
